description: Rishabh Pant's recovery after a severe car accident and a major surgery has led the Indian cricket team to handle his workload cautiously. Despite his aggressive innings in India's second innings, Pant was kept from wicketkeeping to ensure his full recovery.
title: Rohit Sharma wants to be extra careful with Rishabh Pant's injury

description: India faced a dramatic collapse, scoring their lowest home total of 46 against New Zealand in the Bengaluru Test. Despite a strong recovery in the second innings, the team lost, conceding a 107-run target. Skipper Rohit Sharma admitted misjudging the pitch led to the poor performance.
title: 'Yahan koi talwar nahi chalegi': Bhogle tells Rohit

description: On October 21st, 2024, individuals linked to numerology numbers 1 through 9 will experience distinct influences, from heightened leadership skills and emotional sensitivity to a drive for long-term goals and a craving for beauty. Each persona is advised to balance their natural tendencies with caution to ensure harmonious relationships and successful outcomes in personal and professional arenas.
title: Horoscope today, October 21, 2024: Read your astrological predictions

description: Apple's Steve Jobs predicted AI's potential 40 years ago, envisioning machines that think like humans. Jobs spoke at the International Design Conference in 1983 about how studying the human brain could help build better machines. He highlighted the distinction between human consciousness and machine capabilities, fueling ongoing research in artificial intelligence.
title: Apple co-founder Steve Jobs talked about AI 40 years ago: Here’s a video

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, in Varanasi, criticized Congress and Samajwadi Party for dynastic, discriminatory politics while highlighting BJP-led NDA's inclusive governance. He inaugurated 23 projects worth Rs 6,700 crore and emphasized fulfilled promises like the Ram Temple and women's reservation. Modi urged youth participation to eliminate corruption and nepotism.
title: People keep blessing BJP as it works sans bias, says PM, launches Rs 6,700 crore projects in UP

description: IMA president Dr RV Asokan has called for the legalisation of prenatal gender determination tests, citing ineffective results from a decades-old ban. He argues that legalisation, paired with protective measures, can help address India's skewed sex ratio. Asokan questions the current policy's impact and suggests leveraging available technology for better outcomes.
title: IMA chief calls for legalising prenatal gender detection tests

description: Six large Indian states—Uttar Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Maharashtra, Karnataka, Madhya Pradesh, and Rajasthan—accounted for nearly 55% of road deaths in 2023, highlighting an increase in fatalities and underscoring the need for better driver education and more stringent enforcement of traffic laws.
title: Just 6 big states account for 55% of road fatalities in 2023

description: Security forces, in collaboration with Jammu Kashmir Police, neutralized a heavily armed terrorist in Baramulla district, J&K. Recovered items included an AK Rifle, magazines, rounds, pistols and other war-like stores. This operation followed intelligence on a potential infiltration attempt in the Uri area.
title: Security forces kill terrorist in a joint operation in J&K's Baramulla

description: Sanjay Manjrekar criticized Rohit Sharma's captaincy during India's Test loss to New Zealand, particularly his decision to delay bringing on Ravichandran Ashwin. Manjrekar argued that using pacer Mohammed Siraj for extended spells was a tactical error. Despite the defeat, Rohit praised India's second innings comeback. India now needs victories in the next two matches to maintain their home series streak.
title: 'Tactically not his greatest...': Rohit Sharma's tactics questioned

description: The number of individuals reporting taxable income over Rs 1 crore rose significantly from 44,078 in AY2013-14 to nearly 2.3 lakh in AY2023-24, indicating higher incomes and better compliance. Salaried individuals comprised a substantial portion, but higher income levels saw more businessmen and professionals.
title: Crorepati income tax filers soar 5x to 2.3 lakh in 10 years

description: In December 2020, ED's arrest of KA Rauf Sherif sparked a probe into the Popular Front of India's activities, revealing its extensive network across India and abroad. The investigation highlighted PFI's involvement in terror activities, illicit financing through hawala, and arms training camps, leading to multiple arrests and property seizures.
title: 13,000 members, hawala cash: ED files reveal global spread of PFI

description: Mamnoor Airport in Warangal is set to become operational by the end of 2024, being the first of six proposed airports in Telangana. The Telangana government is also progressing on airport projects in Adilabad and Nizamabad, while Bhadrachalam faces delays due to terrain issues. Plans for Devarakadra and Basanthnagar are currently on hold.
title: Grounded for decades, Telangana's historic airport to soar by end of 2024

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 21, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope today, October 21, 2024: Read your astrological predictions
